<item>
            <title>[FELIX-2332] Lots of contention on ExtensionManager.openConnection(URL)</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/FELIX-2332</link>
                <project id="12310100" key="FELIX">Felix</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;This method is synchronized, apparently to protect is the iteration through the m_extensions list. We have seen significant blocking in our applications as this lock encompasses the call to URL.openConnection as well.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;As this list is rarely changed, a copy-on-write structure would be more appropriate, but at the very least the, only holding the lock during the iteration would be far preferable.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment></environment>
        <key id="12464205">FELIX-2332</key>
            <summary>Lots of contention on ExtensionManager.openConnection(URL)</summary>
